<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="173" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,159,361]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis box="[136,867,231,253]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,235,231,252]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">Diagnosis</emphasis>
:—Planta nostra spectabilis, differt a speciebus ceteris sectionis
</emphasis>
Arcticorum 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">
acheniis atropurpureis corpore sparse breviter spinuloso, in pyramidem brevissimam conicam 
<quantity box="[649,763,267,289]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.5 mm</quantity>
longam sensim transeunte, antheris polline carentibus, ligulis saturate luteis tubulosis vel raro subtubulosis, scapis glabris violascentibus, phyllariis involucralibus exterioribus paucis pruinosis et foliis pinnatisectis segmentis lateralibus patentibus.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption box="[136,801,1067,1089]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" startId="2.[136,229,1067,1089]" targetBox="[279,1309,395,1034]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,801,1067,1089]" box="[136,801,1067,1089]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,254,1067,1089]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
Geographical distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[537,795,1068,1089]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[537,795,1068,1089]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">Taraxacum atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="173" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1135,2062]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">
Plants small, slender, usually to 
<quantity box="[510,570,1135,1162]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
, later to 
<quantity box="[675,747,1135,1162]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="cm" value="15.0">15 cm</quantity>
tall. Petiole thin, unwinged, usually purplish, glabrous, tunic absent. Leaves ± mid-green, glabrous, narrowly oblanceolate in outline, ca. 3.5–6 (–9.5) × 0.7–1.7 (–2.0) cm, pinnatipartite to pinnatisect, with 2–4 pairs of patent, narrowly deltoid, subacute lateral segments, distal margin ± straight to subconcave, entire, proximal margin ± straight, usually entire, sometimes with a single basal short triangular tooth; terminal segment broadly triangular to trilobed, lobes ± obtuse; interlobes distinct, 
<quantity box="[1148,1242,1280,1306]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3 mm</quantity>
wide, entire; midvein usually ± suffused purplish. Scapes glabrous, brownish green, often suffused purplish, subequalling leaves. Capitulum mid-yellow to deep yellow, not fully opening, ca. 1 (–1.5) cm wide, florets not numerous (ca. 25–35). Involucre pruinose, greyish olivaceous-green, ca. 
<quantity box="[695,789,1387,1414]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
wide and narrowly rounded to subobconical at base. Outer phyllaries 7–10, posture variable, some ± appressed or loosely appressed, some erect, several or even a majority often erect-arcuate (with recurved distal part), broadly ovate to ovate, ca. (3.5–) 3.7–4.1 (–4.5) × (1.5–) 1.8–2.2 (–2.5) mm, surface strongly pruinose, evenly dark greyish olivaceous green, sometimes dark olivaceous, distally purplish, border not very distinct (sometimes ± absent), white-membranous, ca. 
<quantity box="[849,984,1532,1558]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="0.15" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.2 mm</quantity>
wide, margin glabrous, apex flat. Ligules ± tubular, rarely with a proximal slit, outer ones striped black-purple outside. Stigmas dark discoloured, not exserted. Pollen absent. Achenes blackish purple or very dark grey-purple, ca. 3.9–4.2 × 
<quantity box="[1035,1173,1604,1630]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.8">0.8–0.9 mm</quantity>
, spinulosity very sparse, reaching cone lower (or even middle) part, composed of short, broadly conical spinules usually to 
<quantity box="[1239,1325,1640,1666]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long, body very gradually and indistinctly narrowing into a ± conical cone 
<quantity box="[842,976,1675,1702]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.5 mm</quantity>
long; beak thin (
<quantity box="[1163,1331,1675,1702]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="0.125" valueMax="0.15" valueMin="0.1">0.10–0.15 mm</quantity>
), ca. 
<quantity box="[1387,1452,1676,1702]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
long, pappus white, 
<quantity box="[362,497,1711,1738]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="4.35" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.2">4.2–4.5 mm</quantity>
long. – Agamospermous. – 
<figureCitation box="[812,879,1711,1738]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1276,1298]" captionTargetBox="[228,1355,198,1252]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[202,1385,190,1252]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Taraxacum atropurpureum. General habit (KAM, no. det. 36882, paratype). Scale bar = 2 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641177/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[891,906,1712,1738]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1368,497,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-155@4.[151,1436,497,1899]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Taraxacum atropurpureum. Details of achenes (A, B. KAM, no. det. 36880) and involucre (C. KAM, no. det. 36880). Scale bars:A, C = 1 mm; B = 2 mm. The achene colour has a deeper purple hue when viewed in daylight." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641181/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[919,1022,1712,1738]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1886,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1862]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,190,1862]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Taraxacum atropurpureum in its natural habitat. A. The valley landscape of Tolyatovayam River, locus classicus (in the tent vicinity); B. T. atropurpureum at a mossy microsite among dwarf willows (Salix chamissonis), Tolyatovayam River; C. T. atropurpureum at the Yakotvon’ locality (note the conspicuously pruinose involucre and perfectly tubular, deep yellow ligules); D. T. atropurpureum at the type locality (Tolyatovayam River); E. Landscape below the Yakotvon’ Mts., the paratype locality (the exact site is marked with a pink dot). Photographed by O. Chernyagina, 2011." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641183/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">4B, C, D</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="173" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1135,2062]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,385,1747,1774]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">Diagnostic notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[421,723,1748,1773]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[421,723,1748,1773]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">Taraxacum atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species belonging to the core of 
<emphasis box="[1143,1164,1748,1773]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">T.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1229,1310,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">Arctica</emphasis>
on the basis of a low number of ovate, deep grey-olivaceous, almost unbordered outer phyllaries (without cornicles or horns), slender, low growth, very narrow petioles, and relatively small, dark coloured achenes with a body sparsely spinulose or tuberculate above, with a very gradual transition into a short conical cone, and a relatively short beak.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1135,2062]" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">
The diagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[463,661,1892,1917]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[463,661,1892,1917]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="173">T. atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include tubular, rarely subtubular, deep yellow florets, the absence of pollen, dark stigmas, pruinose outer phyllaries with a very narrow, indistinct border, inner phyllaries pruinose, glabrous leaves and scapes, patent leaf lobes, and, in particular, dark, blackish violet or black-purple achenes with a conical cone 
<quantity box="[136,270,1999,2026]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.5 mm</quantity>
long; the cone is difficult to discern from the achene body because of the very gradual transition and short spinules ascending to the middle part of the cone.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641177" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6641177" box="[136,1162,1276,1298]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641177/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" startId="3.[136,229,1276,1298]" targetBox="[228,1355,198,1252]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1162,1276,1298]" box="[136,1162,1276,1298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,254,1276,1298]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[259,518,1277,1298]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[259,518,1277,1298]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Taraxacum atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. General habit (KAM, no. det. 36882, paratype). Scale bar = 2 cm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="174" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1345,2091]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,1155,1345,1371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">
A more detailed comparison with other members of 
<taxonomicName box="[862,1155,1345,1371]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Arctica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[862,993,1345,1371]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Taraxacum</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1071,1155,1345,1371]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Arctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
:—In several respects, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is close to 
<taxonomicName box="[437,634,1381,1407]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semitubulosum">
<emphasis box="[437,634,1381,1407]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. semitubulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They share tubular florets and the absence of pollen, both being rather rare characters in 
<emphasis box="[333,354,1418,1443]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[415,496,1417,1443]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Arctica</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[510,809,1417,1443]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semitubulosum">
<emphasis box="[510,809,1417,1443]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Taraxacum semitubulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from our plant in its pale yellow flowers, regularly arcuate-recurved, not pruinose, ± borderless outer phyllaries, and leaf segments usually ± recurved to subrecurved; the most conspicuous difference consists in the achene characters, as 
<taxonomicName box="[873,1069,1489,1515]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semitubulosum">
<emphasis box="[873,1069,1489,1515]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. semitubulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has achenes greyish stramineousbrown and much more densely spinulose and squamulose.Another similar species is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahlstedt" authorityYear="1905" box="[1058,1189,1525,1551]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sibiricum">
<emphasis box="[1058,1189,1525,1551]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. sibiricum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, readily distinguishable by its dark grey-brown achenes and polliniferous anthers. Among species lacking pollen, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[1143,1340,1562,1587]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[1143,1340,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[165,286,1598,1623]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mujense">
<emphasis box="[165,286,1598,1623]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. mujense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(distinct in having light red achenes, flat ligules and deltoid leaf lateral segments) and to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jurtzev" authorityYear="1987" box="[1297,1451,1597,1623]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="czukoticum">
<emphasis box="[1297,1451,1597,1623]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. czukoticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ligules flat, leaves narrow, remotely and shallowly lobed).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="174" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1345,2091]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1669,1695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Distribution</emphasis>
:—The distribution range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[656,852,1670,1695]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[656,852,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the basis of the herbarium material, is confined to Karaginskiy District, 
<collectingRegion box="[378,596,1705,1731]" country="Russia" name="Kamchatka" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Kamchatka Region</collectingRegion>
, in the northern part of 
<collectingRegion box="[860,1104,1705,1731]" country="Russia" name="Kamchatka" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Kamchatka Peninsula</collectingRegion>
(see the map on 
<figureCitation box="[1294,1358,1705,1731]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1067,1089]" captionTargetId="figure-113@2.[271,1316,387,1042]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Geographical distribution of Taraxacum atropurpureum." pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="175" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1345,2091]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,245,1741,1767]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Note</emphasis>
:—The report of the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName box="[669,870,1741,1767]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semitubulosum">
<emphasis box="[669,870,1741,1767]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. semitubulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Penzhina River basin, 
<collectingRegion box="[1231,1451,1741,1767]" country="Russia" name="Kamchatka" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Kamchatka Region</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kharkevich, S. S. &amp; Tzvelev, N. N." box="[143,521,1777,1803]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="837 - 843" refId="ref10034" refString="Kharkevich, S. S. &amp; Tzvelev, N. N. (1978) Novye vidy oduvanchika (Taraxacum Wigg.) iz severnoi chasti Kamchatskoi oblasti [New species of Taraxacum from the northern part of the Kamchatka Region]. Botanicheskiy Zhurnal 63 (6): 837 - 843." type="journal article" year="1978">Kharkevich &amp; Tzvelev 1978: 842</bibRefCitation>
), might represent another locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[929,1124,1778,1803]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[929,1124,1778,1803]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and should be checked as the previously known geographical range of 
<taxonomicName box="[599,795,1813,1839]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semitubulosum">
<emphasis box="[599,795,1813,1839]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. semitubulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is almost 
<quantity box="[912,1011,1813,1839]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" unit="km" value="2000.0">2000 km</quantity>
remote from that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[1247,1444,1814,1839]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[1247,1444,1814,1839]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tzvelev, N. N." box="[136,310,1849,1875]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="356 - 409" refId="ref11389" refString="Tzvelev, N. N. (1992) Taraxacum Wigg. In: Kharkevich, S. S. (Ed.) Sosudistye rasteniya sovetskogo Dal'nego Vostoka, vol. 6. Nauka, Sankt-Peterburg, pp. 356 - 409." type="book chapter" year="1992">Tzvelev (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, however, did not include 
<taxonomicName box="[603,798,1849,1875]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semitubulosum">
<emphasis box="[603,798,1849,1875]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. semitubulosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Flora of the Soviet Far East, although the fate of the Penzhina River record was not explicitly explained (the voucher specimen of the Penzhina record has not been located in LE).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1345,2091]" lastBlockId="4.[136,1452,158,473]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="175" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,281,1957,1983]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Habitat</emphasis>
:—The two localities with the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[778,973,1958,1983]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[778,973,1958,1983]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">T. atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were documented in detail. The seemingly low elevation (between 
<quantity box="[409,482,1993,2019]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.18" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" unit="m" value="218.0">218 m</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[539,612,1993,2019]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" unit="m" value="330.0">330 m</quantity>
a.s.l.) nevertheless represents a subalpine vegetation, either a krummholz mosaic with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pall.) Regel" authorityName="Regel" baseAuthorityName="Pall." box="[284,589,2029,2056]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis box="[284,436,2029,2055]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Pinus pumila</emphasis>
(Pall.) Regel
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rupr.) Raus" authorityName="Raus" baseAuthorityName="Rupr." box="[649,1187,2029,2055]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="alnobetula" subSpecies="fruticosa">
<emphasis box="[649,843,2029,2055]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Alnus alnobetula</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[932,1032,2029,2055]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">fruticosa</emphasis>
(Rupr.) Raus
</taxonomicName>
(with patches of snow accumulation and places with a rich subalpine vegetation characterized by 
<taxonomicName box="[970,1140,2065,2091]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Rhodiola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rosea">
<emphasis box="[970,1140,2065,2091]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Rhodiola rosea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName box="[1184,1345,2065,2091]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Oxyria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="digyna">
<emphasis box="[1184,1345,2065,2091]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Oxyria digyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Hill, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gaertn." authorityName="Gaertn." box="[136,467,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Veronica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis box="[136,372,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">Veronica grandiflora</emphasis>
Gaertn.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ledeb." authorityName="Ledeb." box="[480,778,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Primula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuneifolia">
<emphasis box="[480,692,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">Primula cuneifolia</emphasis>
Ledeb.
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="R. Br." authorityName="R. Br." box="[818,1240,158,185]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Cryptogramma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acrostichoides">
<emphasis box="[818,1160,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">Cryptogramma acrostichoides</emphasis>
R. Br.
</taxonomicName>
), or a dwarf-shrub tundra vegetation with scattered snow beds, dominated by 
<taxonomicName authority="(V. N. Vassil.) Kuvaev" authorityName="Kuvaev" baseAuthorityName="V. N. Vassil." box="[797,1447,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Empetrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="nigrum" subSpecies="sibiricum">
<emphasis box="[797,1002,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">Empetrum nigrum</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1088,1194,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">sibiricum</emphasis>
(V.N. Vassil.) Kuvaev
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[136,384,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="4" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uliginosum">
<emphasis box="[136,384,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">Vaccinium uliginosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. or 
<taxonomicName authority="Sukaczev. The" authorityName="Sukaczev. The" box="[454,764,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exilis">
<emphasis box="[454,593,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">Betula exilis</emphasis>
Sukaczev. The
</taxonomicName>
microsites inhabited by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschner, Stepanek, Buryy, Chernyagina &amp; Efimov" authorityYear="2022" box="[1039,1236,231,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="atropurpureum">
<emphasis box="[1039,1236,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">T. atropurpureum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
typically represent open, sometimes mossy snow-bed patches, with 
<taxonomicName authority="Andersson" authorityName="Andersson" box="[700,1032,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chamissonis">
<emphasis box="[700,903,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">Salix chamissonis</emphasis>
Andersson
</taxonomicName>
at the 
<typeStatus box="[1117,1165,267,293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">type</typeStatus>
locality, and with a rich subalpine vegetation at the other site.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="175" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,473]" pageId="4" pageNumber="175">
